definitions.definition: A major Germanic god, often described as chief of the pantheon, in his Norse form a member of the Æsir , married to Frigg and associated with knowledge, poetry and war. Wednesday refers to him by way of interpretatio germanica .
A mountain on Baffin Island , Canada .
